01:31:42,300 --> 01:31:45,300
the gravitational field inside the shell

1511
01:31:45,300 --> 01:31:47,300
would be that of empty space

1512
01:31:47,300 --> 01:31:49,300
and the gravitational field outside

1513
01:31:49,300 --> 01:31:51,300
would look exactly like the point mass

1514
01:31:51,300 --> 01:31:54,300
it would just be the place where you go from outside to inside

1515
01:31:54,300 --> 01:31:56,300
which would change with time

1516
01:31:56,300 --> 01:31:59,300
so in particular if you had a time dependent shell of mass

1517
01:31:59,300 --> 01:32:01,300
which was contracting

1518
01:32:01,300 --> 01:32:04,300
with the mass staying fixed

1519
01:32:04,300 --> 01:32:06,300
then outside it

1520
01:32:06,300 --> 01:32:08,300
you would see the point mass gravitational field

1521
01:32:08,300 --> 01:32:10,300
inside you would see nothing

1522
01:32:10,300 --> 01:32:14,300
only the boundary between the two regions would change with time

1523
01:32:14,300 --> 01:32:17,300
the same exact thing is true in general relativity

1524
01:32:17,300 --> 01:32:18,300
almost the same thing

1525
01:32:18,300 --> 01:32:21,300
close, not quite, but close

1526
01:32:21,300 --> 01:32:25,300
so let me tell you what is called Berkhoff's theorem

1527
01:32:25,300 --> 01:32:29,300
and then the next time we will combine Berkhoff's theorem

1528
01:32:29,300 --> 01:32:31,300
with these two diagrams

1529
01:32:31,300 --> 01:32:35,300
and put together the theory of how a black hole is formed

1530
01:32:38,300 --> 01:32:41,300
so get Berkhoff's theorem, remember it

1531
01:32:41,300 --> 01:32:43,300
what does it say?

1532
01:32:43,300 --> 01:32:47,300
it says if you have a spherically symmetric distribution of mass

1533
01:32:48,300 --> 01:32:52,300
what do you see inside the spherically symmetric distribution of mass?

1534
01:32:52,300 --> 01:32:56,300
exactly what you would see if there was no mass at all

1535
01:32:56,300 --> 01:32:58,300
flat spacetime

1536
01:32:58,300 --> 01:33:00,300
empty space

1537
01:33:00,300 --> 01:33:02,300
flat

1538
01:33:02,300 --> 01:33:06,300
Minkowski, whatever you want to call it

1539
01:33:06,300 --> 01:33:11,300
just the solution of Einstein's theory with absolutely nothing there

1540
01:33:11,300 --> 01:33:13,300
just good old empty space

1541
01:33:13,300 --> 01:33:14,300
inside

1542
01:33:14,300 --> 01:33:16,300
what about on the outside, what do you see?

1543
01:33:17,300 --> 01:33:20,300
do you see a Newtonian gravitational field?

1544
01:33:21,300 --> 01:33:23,300
no, not quite

1545
01:33:23,300 --> 01:33:25,300
what do you think you see on the outside?

1546
01:33:29,300 --> 01:33:33,300
it's spherical mass, but what's the gravitational field on the outside?

1547
01:33:34,300 --> 01:33:35,300
Schwarzschild

1548
01:33:36,300 --> 01:33:41,300
in other words, the metric on the inside is exactly that of flat space

1549
01:33:41,300 --> 01:33:43,300
and the metric on the outside is exactly that of flat space

1550
01:33:43,300 --> 01:33:46,300
and the metric on the outside is exactly that of the Schwarzschild black hole

1551
01:33:46,300 --> 01:33:49,300
we can write it

1552
01:33:49,300 --> 01:33:57,300
on the inside we have good old the t squared minus the x squared, the y squared, the z squared

1553
01:33:57,300 --> 01:34:01,300
and on the outside we have Schwarzschild

1554
01:34:01,300 --> 01:34:03,300
I'm not going to write it

1555
01:34:05,300 --> 01:34:09,300
I think I could have written the metric faster than I could have written Schwarzschild

1556
01:34:09,300 --> 01:34:11,300
right

1557
01:34:11,300 --> 01:34:16,300
in other words, we piece together two things

1558
01:34:16,300 --> 01:34:19,300
both of which we know very well

1559
01:34:19,300 --> 01:34:22,300
connected together by a shell

1560
01:34:22,300 --> 01:34:26,300
how about the mass of the Schwarzschild solution?

1561
01:34:26,300 --> 01:34:30,300
Schwarzschild solution has a mass associated with it

1562
01:34:30,300 --> 01:34:33,300
it's just the mass of the total shell

1563
01:34:33,300 --> 01:34:35,300
does the mass of the shell change with time?

1564
01:34:35,300 --> 01:34:38,300
even if it moves, even if the shell contracts?

1565
01:34:39,300 --> 01:34:42,300
does the total mass of the shell change with time?

1566
01:34:42,300 --> 01:34:43,300
why not?

1567
01:34:46,300 --> 01:34:52,300
well supposing I tell you, supposing I just mutter the words E equals mc squared

1568
01:34:53,300 --> 01:34:55,300
conservation of energy

1569
01:34:55,300 --> 01:34:56,300
right

1570
01:34:56,300 --> 01:34:59,300
the mass, the total mass of that shell

1571
01:34:59,300 --> 01:35:01,300
even if the shell, and can the shell change?

1572
01:35:01,300 --> 01:35:03,300
of course the shell can change

1573
01:35:03,300 --> 01:35:05,300
you build yourself a shell

1574
01:35:05,300 --> 01:35:09,300
but the shell isn't strong enough to maintain itself against the gravitational force

1575
01:35:09,300 --> 01:35:11,300
if it's in the field, what happens?

1576
01:35:11,300 --> 01:35:13,300
it starts to collapse

1577
01:35:13,300 --> 01:35:16,300
as it collapses, the mass doesn't change

1578
01:35:16,300 --> 01:35:19,300
but the radius of it changes

1579
01:35:19,300 --> 01:35:23,300
what was inside was just good old flat space

1580
01:35:23,300 --> 01:35:26,300
what was outside was Schwarzschild

1581
01:35:26,300 --> 01:35:32,300
and the boundary between the two behaviors might change with time

1582
01:35:32,300 --> 01:35:37,300
so what we're going to do next time is we're going to take the flat space solution

1583
01:35:37,300 --> 01:35:40,300
that's the inside

1584
01:35:40,300 --> 01:35:43,300
and patch it together with the outside

1585
01:35:43,300 --> 01:35:45,300
which is the Schwarzschild solution

1586
01:35:45,300 --> 01:35:47,300
I'll show you how to do that

1587
01:35:47,300 --> 01:35:49,300
and in that way we will learn

1588
01:35:49,300 --> 01:35:52,300
in a very simple example how a black hole is formed

1589
01:35:52,300 --> 01:35:55,300
we'll find that half of this diagram doesn't mean anything

1590
01:35:55,300 --> 01:35:57,300
but we'll come to it next time

1591
01:35:57,300 --> 01:36:00,300
so, formation of a black hole next time

1592
01:36:02,300 --> 01:36:04,300
okay

1593
